{
  "artifact": "qurl-agent-registration-golden-vectors",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "NHP agent-registration Noise-handshake golden packets (X25519 / AES-256-GCM / BLAKE2s): the OTP request, the emailed-code and pre-issued-key REG requests, and the server register-ack (RAK) success and error replies.",
  "source_of_truth": "github.com/layervai/qurl-conformance",
  "notes": [
    "otp / reg_emailed / reg_preissued: DETERMINISTIC. A conformant initiator MUST reproduce packet_hex byte-for-byte from the listed inputs (fixed ephemeral_priv, counter, timestamp_nanos, preamble). These packets are decrypt-fenced by the NHP Go server responder, which independently recovers the initiator static key, timestamp, and body.",
    "reg_emailed vs reg_preissued: the two REG packets differ ONLY in the body `otp` value (an emailed 8-digit code vs a pre-issued key secret). They are identical on the wire; a verifier distinguishes them by the matched key record, not by the packet bytes. Documented so a consumer sees both paths use the same NHP_REG packet framing.",
    "rak_success / rak_error: FROZEN decrypt-only. The server sealed these with a RANDOM server ephemeral, so they are NOT reproducible by a client; a consumer can only DECRYPT them and MUST recover type=NHP_RAK (14), the counter, the timestamp_nanos, and the body (ServerRegisterAckMsg: errCode/errMsg/aspId). Re-hosted here verbatim as frozen golden values, mirroring the relay-knock `ack` precedent.",
    "conformance#19 matched-counter pair: rak_success AND rak_error carry counter_hex = 0xb, which ECHOES reg_emailed.counter (11). The reg_emailed -> rak pair is therefore counter-matched, so a consumer validating the counter-echo enforcement (a RAK must echo its REG's transaction counter) has a positive fixture.",
    "Origin: OTP/REG built by a type-parameterized NHP initiator with a fixed ephemeral/counter/timestamp (a conformant initiator reproduces packet_hex byte-for-byte); RAK sealed by the OpenNHP reference server with a fixed transaction counter and a random ephemeral, so it is frozen decrypt-only. Keys/ids/secrets are SYNTHETIC (fixed fill patterns, distinct from the relay-knock set) — no real keys, emails, or hostnames.",
    "Fence status: the authoritative independent fence for these packets today is the OpenNHP reference server decrypt suite, which recovers the initiator static key / timestamp / type / body from every case. An in-repo BEHAVIORAL fence that rebuilds the deterministic OTP/REG packet_hex and re-decrypts it (as relay_knock's does) is deferred until a type-parameterized single-message builder is exposed to this repo's verify SDK; tracked in layervai/qurl-conformance#21."
  ],
